events.name: LA Clippers at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — RJ Barrett had 28 points, 14 rebounds and six assists, and the New York Knicks beat the Los Angeles Clippers 110-102 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Barrett scores 28 as Knicks beat Clippers 110-102

headlines.description: — This was quite a way for Jayson Tatum to break out of his shooting slump.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum scores 51 in Celtics' 116-87 rout of Wizards

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Miami Heat

headlines.description: — The Miami Heat knew the run was coming. Even early in the fourth quarter, with a 23-point lead, Heat players were telling each other that the game wasn't over.
headlines.shortLinkText: Heat waste most of big lead, hold on to top Lakers 113-107

headlines.description: — Moritz Wagner scored 23 points, younger brother Franz Wagner added 18, and the Orlando Magic defeated the short-handed Chicago Bulls 114-95 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wagner brothers combine for 41 points as Magic beat Bulls

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Toronto Raptors

headlines.description: — CJ McCollum had 19 points and 10 rebounds, Jusuf Nurkic had 11 points and 11 rebounds for his fifth straight double-double, and the Portland Trail Blazers beat the Toronto Raptors 114-105 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: McCollum, Nurkic lead Trail Blazers over Raptors, 114-105

headlines.description: — Trae Young scored 30 points and tied a season-high with eight 3-pointers, and the streaky Atlanta Hawks defeated the cold-shooting Charlotte Hornets 113-91 on Sunday night for their fourth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young scores 30, Hawks hammer cold-shooting Hornets 113-91

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had 38 points and 12 rebounds and the Philadelphia 76ers held off a late rally to beat the San Antonio Spurs 115-109 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid's double-double helps 76ers hold off Spurs, 115-109

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had 37 points, 11 rebounds and nine assists and Kristaps Porzingis had 15 points, eight rebounds and a season-best six blocks as the Dallas Mavericks shut down the Memphis Grizzlies to win 104-91 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic, Porzingis lead Mavericks past Grizzlies 104-91

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored 25 points, D’Angelo Russell had 23 points and 10 assists, and the Minnesota Timberwolves defeated the Brooklyn Nets 136-125 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Edwards, Russell team up to lead Wolves past Nets, 136-125
Jokic scores 34 points, Nuggets beat Pistons 117-111

events.name: Utah Jazz at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry has been around long enough that he can be playful when it comes to his rare, recent shooting funk.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jordan Poole scores 20 points, Warriors hold off Jazz 94-92
